Pretty well the same, yes, I don't think there was much difference in them - I didn't go in their homes but judging from their appearance I couldn't see any difference in them to me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9647720 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944549\charrsid5711483 Did the t
eachers ever single out some children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16153517 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944549\charrsid5711483 
Well, I can't think of any particular case but it - it is looked on that some teachers don't like certain children, possibly through the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13660561\charrsid5711483 children\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944549\charrsid5711483  own fault, we don't know. B
ut that can happen - you get a - boy a little bit naughty and the teacher takes a dislike to him and then of course he can do no right after that.
