No, I don't think I would. I think I was glad to get away from school in a way - I wanted to get out and do some work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9647720 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944549\charrsid5711483 But you did have the opportunity - your mother couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid16153517 AC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944549\charrsid5711483 
Ah that was scholarship, yes, she wouldn't - she wouldn't go in for scholarships - she didn't think it was good for me. Well - it's what they call I expect their 'O' levels now or something, I don't know. We call it the scholars
hip and you went in for a certain examination, if you passed it, well you were more or less upgraded a little but - my mother didn't think - that - it was doing good for a boy to be overtaxed with a lot of education on top of the other like that you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid9647720 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid14944549\charrsid5711483 You'd have gone at school if you'd taken up the scholarship?
